%h3 Terminal Commands
= link_to 'rbenv commands', 'https://karloespiritu.github.io/cheatsheets/rbenv/', target: :_blank

%p
  Check which version of Bundler is in Directory
  %br/
  %code bundle -v

%p
  Check for which version of rails you have on system
  %br/
  %code ruby -v

%p
  List all the Ruby versions know to rbenv
  %br/
  %code rbenv version
  %br/

%p
  Displays the currently active Ruby version
  %br/
  %code rbenv versions

%p
  Install the latest bundler
  %br/
  %code gem install bundler

%p
  Check Gem List
  %br/
  %code gem list

%p
  Installs the latest rails in directory
  %br/
  %code gem install rail

%p
  Installs latest gems
  %br/
  %code bundle install

%hr/

%h3 STEPS
%p
  Go to Gits folder
  %br/
  %code cd ~/Gits

%p
  Change the version of Ruby we are using for that console session ONLY
  %br/
  %code rbenv shell 3.1.2

%p
  Build a new directory and installs Ruby
  %br/
  %code rails new NEW_PROJECT

%p
  Go to new directory
  %br/
  %code cd NEW_PROJECT

%p
  Start Server
  %br/
  %code rails s

%hr/

